Interface AbstractBooleanPredicate1<P extends AbstractBooleanPredicate1<P>>

    @InheritOnly
public interface AbstractBooleanPredicate1<P extends AbstractBooleanPredicate1<P>>
extends AbstractPredicateN<P>, net.ashwork.functionality.partial.InputChainableInput<java.lang.Boolean>, net.ashwork.functionality.partial.FunctionVariant<java.lang.Boolean,net.ashwork.functionality.operator.primitive.booleans.BooleanOperator1>, net.ashwork.functionality.partial.UnboxedInput<AbstractPredicate1<java.lang.Boolean,?>>
    Represents a predicate that accepts a boolean-valued argument and produces a boolean-valued result. This is the one-arity specialization for AbstractPredicateN. This is the predicate specialization for BooleanOperator1. This is the boolean-consuming primitive specialization of AbstractPredicate1.
    Since:
    1.0.0
    See Also:
    AbstractPredicateN, BooleanOperator1, AbstractPredicate1
    API Note:
    This is an abstract predicate and should not be used directly. It should instead be called by one of its subtypes.
